{:title "Signed Audit Trail (The 'Fact' Log)"
 :description "An append-only, HMAC-signed record of all system events to ensure non-repudiation and visibility."
 :philosophy "Event Sourcing (Linear Facts), Data-centric (NDJSON), Content-addressed signatures."
 :inspired-by "Talon (Evidence), Rich Hickey (Value of Information)"
 :implementation-strategy
 {:format :ndjson
  :storage "logs/audit.log.ndjson"
  :fields [:id :timestamp :type :data :sig]
  :signing-alg "HmacSHA256"}
 :acceptance-criteria
 ["Every LLM call, tool execution, and policy decision is recorded as an immutable 'Fact'."
  "Signature covers the current event + the signature of the previous event (Chaining)."
  "Human-readable NDJSON format for easy grepping and inspection."
  "Cost and token usage tracking integrated as first-class events."
  "Signature verification tool: `bb verify-audit-log`."]
 :edge-cases
 ["Key rotation: How to verify old logs with a new key?"
  "Log rotation: Breaking the signature chain during file rotation."
  "Disk pressure: Automatic compression/archival of old logs."]
 :depends-on [:pii-redaction]}
